Russian inflation down in first quarter 
Russian inflation continued to fall in the first three months of the
year, reaching 5.3 percent for the quarter, compared with 10 percent in
the first quarter of last year, it was announced on Wednesday.
The state statistics commission said that inflation in March was 1.4
percent, down from 1.5 percent in February and from 2.3 percent a month
earlier.
Inflation for 1996 as a whole was 21.8 percent, down from 131 percent
the previous year.
The government's aim is to reduce inflation to 12 percent this year.
